messages.messageBody:
well, I am not "in" melaleuca right now...couldn't
afford it. :) But I buy the products when I can from
others I know who are in it sometimes. Haven't for a
really long time, though. Heeh, though I'm just now
finishing up a bottle of oil that we still had from
teh dayz when we stockpiled all teh products...mom
still has some lotion in the older packaging, I think.
:)
And cool beans for another short family. That's us. I
was so happy when I outgrew my oldest sister at 4'
11", and my dad's mom was about your height. Though my
boyfriend is not my kids father (my ex husband was 5'
10"), he is kinda short for a guy, I'm told (who knows
or cares what "average" is...and so me and my kids and
him make a cute little short family. :)
My son was born in May, too, btw. Co-ink-i-dinks are
everywhere.
-Bobbie

messages.messageBody:
We used to order from Melaleuca too. But since the move from Washington to Montana and a much lower income, I haven't been able to order anything. I don't even have the information anymore. Maybe some day we can order from them again. I do like their antiseptic products...though Naomi hates the smell of the oil. LOL!
Jessica

From: Sherry Hagen <oilmagic@...>

Subject: [Unschooling-dotcom] Skinny boy

Hi Bobbie,

It's nice to hear about another person with Melaleuca.  I've been a
customer for 5 years and I'm a Director 2, earning about $500 a month.
Since I'm 4' 9" and my husbands was always the shortest in his class
(he's 5'9" now) much son is on the short end.  He's actually solid
muscle, though my mom might call him a skinny boy.  A father was telling
someone that he could guess any child's age correctly now that he was a
parent and pointed to my son and said she was 5.  I turned around and
said, "Sorry, he'll be 7 years old near the end of May."

Sherry

Hi Bobbie,

It's nice to hear about another person with Melaleuca. I've been a
customer for 5 years and I'm a Director 2, earning about $500 a month.
Since I'm 4' 9" and my husbands was always the shortest in his class
(he's 5'9" now) much son is on the short end. He's actually solid
muscle, though my mom might call him a skinny boy. A father was telling
someone that he could guess any child's age correctly now that he was a
parent and pointed to my son and said she was 5. I turned around and
said, "Sorry, he'll be 7 years old near the end of May."

Sherry
